ActAn Act to amend the Marine Liability Act and the Federal Courts Act and to make consequential amendments to other Acts
SubjectOrder Fixing the Date of the Coming into Force of Certain Sections of the Act
PrecisOrder which fixes, as the day on which sections 11, 13, 17 and 19 to 23 of AN ACT TO AMEND THE MARINE LIABILITY ACT AND THE FEDERAL COURTS ACT AND TO MAKE CONSEQUENTIAL AMENDMENTS TO OTHER ACTS come into force, the first day on which both the International Convention on Civil Liability for Bunker Oil Pollution Damage, 2001, and the Protocol of 2003 to the International Convention on the Establishment of an International Fund for Compensation for Oil Pollution Damage, 1992, are in force in Canada.
RegistrationRegistration: SI/ 2009-0102 Publication Date: 2009-10-14
